{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"alias":"centaurian-dunite-coati","description":"## Why\n\nExternal creation paths have different semantics from local facades. A Jira issue materialized locally is a jira creation, while an existing local ticket later pushed to Jira keeps its original channel. NDJSON import creates a fresh local record through import while source_* continues to describe the prior store. Historical Jira records need a conservative answer without rewriting shared event history.\n\n## What\n\n- Add creation_channel=jira to the CREATE data assembled only by the inbound Jira materialization path in src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/apply_inbound_records.py. Reconciler-created placeholder identities produced as part of inbound materialization also receive jira explicitly.\n- Preserve the original cli, mcp, or python channel when a local ticket is later bound or pushed outbound to Jira; sync direction must not rewrite genesis provenance.\n- Have src/rebar/_io/import_ndjson.py invoke the shared library creation path with the internal import channel. The newly created local ticket reports import even when the exported source record contains another creation_channel. Existing source_id/source_created_at/source_author/source_env behavior remains unchanged.\n- Add one reducer helper for legacy channel projection. When creation_channel is missing, infer jira only if ticket_id starts with jira-, author equals reconciler, and env_id equals reconciler. All comparisons are exact. On that match set creation_channel=jira and creation_channel_inferred=true; on every mismatch set creation_channel=unknown and omit the marker.\n- Base inference only on creation-stable state. Do not inspect current tags, current Jira bindings, source_* fields, comments, or mutable reconciler state.\n- Add positive and one-signal-at-a-time negative tests so a locally crafted title/tag/binding cannot trigger inference.\n- Document recorded versus inferred Jira provenance and the import/source_* distinction.\n\n## Approach Rationale\n\nNew external writers declare their channel because they know it exactly. Historical inference is limited to the deterministic ID/author/environment conjunction already produced by the legacy reconciler: inbound_translate._jira_key_to_local_id generates jira-* IDs and _event_meta defaults both author and env_id to reconciler. Requiring all three signals prioritizes zero false positives; overridden or incomplete legacy metadata intentionally returns unknown.\n\n## Scope\n\nIN: Jira inbound CREATE, Jira-side-effect identity creation, outbound non-rewrite behavior, NDJSON import, full-log legacy Jira inference, negative controls, export/import semantics, and documentation.\n\nOUT: guessing historical local channels, mutating old events, treating Jira binding as creation, SNAPSHOT-only legacy inference, compaction, and new filtering/reporting surfaces.\n\n## Files\n\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/apply_inbound_records.py and inbound_translate.py call sites: recorded Jira channel and side-effect identities.\n- src/rebar/_io/import_ndjson.py and _io/_provenance.py: recorded import channel while preserving source_*.\n- src/rebar/reducer/_processors.py: shared deterministic legacy projection helper.\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py: Jira inbound/outbound and inference controls.\n- tests/interfaces/io/test_creation_channel.py: import/export behavior.\n- docs/event-schema.md and docs/cli-reference.md: Jira/import semantics.\n\n## Dependencies\n\nDepends on the local-contract story because it supplies the enum, writer validation, reducer field, and public output contract.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] A newly materialized inbound Jira issue and any placeholder identity created by that path persist creation_channel=jira, independent of reconciler author/env overrides. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py -k \"inbound and recorded\".\n- [ ] Binding or pushing an existing cli/mcp/python ticket to Jira never changes its stored or projected creation_channel. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py -k outbound.\n- [ ] NDJSON import persists creation_channel=import on the new local CREATE, preserves source_* provenance, and does not copy the exported source ticket channel into the new local channel. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/io/test_creation_channel.py -k import.\n- [ ] A legacy full-log ticket with no recorded channel projects jira plus creation_channel_inferred=true only when jira-* ID, reconciler author, and reconciler env_id all match exactly. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py -k legacy_positive.\n- [ ] Removing or changing each inference signal independently produces creation_channel=unknown with no inference marker; tags, bindings, source_* metadata, and titles never affect the decision. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_creation_channel.py -k legacy_negative.\n- [ ] Existing import idempotency and reconciler inbound behavior remain green. Prove with uv run pytest -q tests/interfaces/io/test_import_idempotency.py tests/interfaces/io/test_import_ndjson.py tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/mutate/test_inbound_leaf_bodies.py.","id":"e622-a596-3ceb-4f74","parent_id":"jira-reb-977","priority":2,"tags":["provenance","audit","jira"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"Attribute Jira/import creation and infer legacy Jira origins"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784259059863571001,"uuid":"bd59a983-0819-4b3b-96d0-50c5a9867f4d"}